  <text>
    <body>
      <p>
        <s>The play <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="title">Disgraced, Scene 3</ref>, written by <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="author">Ayad Akhtar</ref>, published in <date>2018</date> is set in <name type="geo">New York</name> in the <date>2013s</date>.</s>
        <s>The central conflict in <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="title">Disgraced, Scene 3</ref> are generated by the prejudices that characterize <name type="geo"><choice><orig>Americas</orig><reg>America's</reg></choice></name> culture and politics in the post <name type="misc">9/11</name> era.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>The final part of scene 3 <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="line">(p. 71, l. 12 - p. 74, l. 25)</ref> starts with <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Isaac</ref> and <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Emily</ref> kissing, they get interrupted by <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Jory</ref>, <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Isaac's</ref> wife and <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref>, <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Emily's</ref> husband.</s>
        <s>They all start arguing, first about the question if <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Isaac</ref> really kissed <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Emily</ref> and lately about the injustice that <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> <choice><orig>feel</orig><reg>feels</reg></choice>.</s>
        <s><ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> spits in <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Isaac's</ref> face and <choice><orig>say</orig><reg>says</reg></choice> to <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Jory</ref> that they should go.</s>
        <s><ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Jory</ref><choice><orig>say</orig><reg>says</reg></choice> on her walk out that their boss is retiring and that she <choice><orig>become</orig><reg>becomes</reg></choice> his caseload, because <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> is duplicitous.</s>
        <s><ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> and <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Emily</ref> still are arguing till the point where <ref target="b11gk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> starts hitting in his <choice><orig>wife</orig><reg>wife's</reg></choice> face.</s>
        <s>He stops when his <choice><orig>Nephew</orig><reg>nephew</reg></choice> knocks at the door.</s>
      </p>
